HEADWORD: Cinquecentist
<hw>Cin`que*cen"tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An Italian of the sixteenth century, esp. a poet or
artist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A student or imitator of the art or literature of
the Cinquecento.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinquecento</ent>⟦br⟧
